Hello folks, I got to know that you will need to upload your cv/resume for your internship application, I'll provide mine, you can edit & upload it.
Remember, don't ever refrain from applying to any internship, if you see a huge Job Description (JD), don't get afraid, just tell the interviewer you are ready to learn whatever they want.

During 1st year, everyone's resume is empty. Here is a way:
1. Look for the post you are applying to, say Front End Web Developer.
2. Now you don't know skills needed 
3. Go onto google search skills needed, watch some tutorials.
4. Get to know if you will love the job, put that on your resume, if you get selected for interview, tell them you know the basics and will learn more.
5. Time ke sath samajh jaoge ki Internships will teach you 10x times more than what you learn from college.
6. There you go, everyone please never in your life ever refrain from applying, reject krna unka kam hai, hamara nahi, keep the attitude that I'll learn, mujhe ye kam pasand hai, to me seekh lunga kaise hota hai. That's it.

messages.text:
Look folks, let me make one thing very very clear, make sure that in future whatever skill you gain in college or yourself, is it the need of future, will companies be hiring for that skill, then grow that skill set. College will teach you many things that will not be even needed, we are being taught web designing that took load of year 2000, is it needed, NO.
Everyone who is doing something in college, taking paid projects in development, or is working on an internship somewhere, are self taught programmers, they did following:
1. Find what you wanna do.
2. Say you wanna become web developer.
3. Search the skills needed on internet.
4. Pick up a tutorial (preferably from Udemy)
5. Stick to that course, until you complete it, those who complete the course are on completely the other side, from those who just think about completing it.
6. Don't sleep at night till you accomplish the goal you made, say you thought you'll complete 30 Hour course in 2 months, that is 30 minutes everyday, don't sleep before that, time you're spending here is what you are investing in your future.
7. Honestly, those are achieving top ranks in class, always sit with their hand on hand for college to teach skill, and college never does that, it is made to teach you syllabus and give you a degree, you'll realize this soon.
8. There you go on your path to become a self taught programmer.
9. Sometime soon, I'll post on how to receive the most trending/hot skills of market.
